25|$|During the 2011 deployment, {{aircraft}} from Carrier Air Wing One flew 7764 sorties, {{with more}} than 7120 combat sorties in support of Operation Enduring Freedom in Afghanistan. Units of Carrier Strike Group Twelve also disrupted nine <b>piracy</b> <b>attacks,</b> resulting in the capture of 75 suspected pirates and the detention of an additional 18 suspected pirates. Also during this deployment, the guided-missile destroyer Barry was detached from Carrier Strike Group Twelve in order to participate in Operation Odyssey Dawn. During that operation, on 19 March 2011, Barry was credited with launching the 2000th Tomahawk land-attack cruise missile.|$|R
