50|$|Due to the {{frequent}} <b>piracy</b> <b>attacks</b> {{to the local}} navigation and the civil conflicts affecting China, in 1927 the Portuguese Navy reinforced its station at Macau. Besides the deployment of additional war ships, a decision was taken to include an air force of Fairey III seaplanes in the Portuguese naval forces at Macau. To serve as its base, a naval air station was installed at the Taipa Island. The main activities of this air force was the patrol of the Pearl River Delta, chasing pirates and smugglers, but it also conducted some missions over the China Seas, China Mainland, Hong-Kong and French Indochina. This force was deactivated in 1932.|$|R
